  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Architecture Designer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description: </strong></p><ul><li>Oversees the architectural elements of a project, including its design and feasibility.</li><li>Meeting, work closely with clients to understand the requirements of projects. </li><li>Develop project plans and budgets for projects including architectural drawings, specifications, estimates, cost reports, schedule, material documents, and specification lists for client approval.</li><li>Visiting the site regularly to ensure construction adheres to state regulations.</li><li>Ensuring the project remains on time and within specifications.</li><li>Creating progress reports, time schedules, and revised budgets.</li><li>Coordinate with Project Manager on daily updates and weekly reports on the work progress and issues on site, including necessary checklist and documentations.</li><li>Coordinate, preparation of tender, evaluation, recommendation, and award processes.</li><li>Maintain proper records of all site files on project correspondences, documents and drawings for easy retrieval and reference.</li><li>Prepare and update the list of outstanding / non-compliance works for submission to the Architect / Management for discussion during site meetings on regular basis.</li><li>Ensure all work is carried out to the requirements of the client, with the design team working to the correct specifications and delivering a high quality and timely product to the client. </li><li>Adaptable and problem solving, managing internal and external stakeholders, manage risks and issues, and monitor progress to ensure that the project stays on track.</li><li>Suggest innovative solutions to improve sustainability, efficiency, or aesthetics.</li><li>Conducting a final inspection after the project is complete.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Jobs Requirements: </strong></p><ul><li>Min master’s degree in architecture, design, or similar.</li><li>3-5 Years Experience Preferred. </li><li>Local Project <u><em>with some overseas experience</em></u><strong> </strong>preferred.</li><li>State architecture certification.</li><li>Portfolio of completed projects (hospitality & commercial work experience preferred) </li><li>Advanced knowledge of drafting software including AutoCAD and SketchUp.</li><li>Excellent communication and reporting skills.</li><li>Ability to translate concepts into functional construction designs.</li><li>Advanced project-management skills.</li><li>Strong problem-solving and analytical skills.</li><li>Must be able to speak <strong>English, Mandarin, Cantonese. </strong></li><li>Ability to coordinate with multiple stakeholders daily.</li><li><u><em>Must be able to travel overseas for work occasionally.</em></u></li></ul>",
